𝗞𝗼𝗯𝗲 𝗕𝗲𝗲𝗳 is a special grade of beef that comes from the Tajima-gyu breed of cattle found in Japan’s Hyogo Prefecture. Introduced as work animals in the rice cultivation industry during the 2nd Century, Tajima-gyu became isolated from other breeds, hiding away in Japan’s mountainous landscape in small pockets of cultivable land.

This isolation is said to be responsible for a completely unique taste and texture; one that depicts Kobe beef as the ultimate meat when it comes to flavour, tenderness, and high amounts of intramuscular fat.
